i' in 'tide'">a=C9=AA</span><span title=3D"/=C9=A1/: 'g' in 'guy'">=C9=A1</=
span><span title=3D"/=C9=99n/: 'on' in 'button'">=C9=99n</span></span>-/</a=
></span></span> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Pronunciation=
_respelling_key" title=3D"Help:Pronunciation respelling key"><i title=3D"En=
glish pronunciation respelling"><span style=3D"font-size:90%">EYE</span>-g=
=C9=99n-</i></a>) or <b>characteristic vector</b> is a (nonzero) <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector_(mathematics_and_physics)" title=3D"V=
ector (mathematics and physics)">vector</a> that has its <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Direction_(geometry)" title=3D"Direction (geometry)"=
>direction</a> unchanged (or reversed) by a given <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Linear_map" title=3D"Linear map">linear transformation</a>.=
 More precisely, an eigenvector <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-el=
ement-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" s=
tyle=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" =
alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbf {v} }">
  <semantics>
