 <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BB</i><sub><i>n</i></sub></span>, each of w=
hich is an eigenvalue, may not all be distinct. (The number of times an eig=
envalue appears is known as its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ei=
genvalues_and_eigenvectors#Algebraic_multiplicity">algebraic multiplicity</=
a>.)
</p><p>As a brief example, which is described in more detail in the example=
s section later, consider the matrix
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
