t-style:italic;">=CE=BB</span> can be found by solving for the components o=
f <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>v</b></span> in the equation <span class=3D"te=
xhtml">(<i>A</i> =E2=88=92 <i>=CE=BBI</i>)<b>v</b> =3D <b>0</b></span>. In =
this example, the eigenvectors are any nonzero scalar multiples of
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \mathbf {v} _{\lambda =3D1}=3D{\begin{bmatrix}1\\-1\end{bmatrix=
}},\quad \mathbf {v} _{\lambda =3D3}=3D{\begin{bmatrix}1\\1\end{bmatrix}}.}=
">
