pan></span> matrix. Any row vector <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>u</b></span> =
satisfying this equation is called a <b><dfn>left eigenvector</dfn></b> of =
<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span> and <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=BA</span> is its =
associated eigenvalue. Taking the transpose of this equation,
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle A^{\textsf {T}}\mathbf {u} ^{\textsf {T}}=3D\kappa \mathbf {u} =
^{\textsf {T}}.}">
