            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CE=BA<!-- =CE=BA --></mi>
        <msup>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi mathvariant=3D"bold">u</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
              <mtext mathvariant=3D"sans-serif">T</mtext>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A^{\textsf {T=
}}\mathbf {u} ^{\textsf {T}}=3D\kappa \mathbf {u} ^{\textsf {T}}.}</annotat=
ion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c0fc4d00ecb8d5fdac2710d2e4156b66214ba3f5" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.338ex; width:13.852ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
^{\textsf {T}}\mathbf {u} ^{\textsf {T}}=3D\kappa \mathbf {u} ^{\textsf {T}=
}.}"></span>
</p><p>Comparing this equation to equation (<b><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Eigenvalues_and_eigenvectors#math_1">1</a></b>), it follows im=
mediately that a left eigenvector of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">A</span> is the same as the transpose of a right eigenv=
ector of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i><sup>T</sup></span>, with the same=
 eigenvalue. Furthermore, since the characteristic polynomial of <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i><sup>T</sup></span> is the same as the characteristic=
 polynomial of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A<=
/span>, the left and right eigenvectors of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" sty=
le=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span> are associated with the same eigenvalues=
.
</p>
