<span class=3D"texhtml"><b>v</b><sub>1</sub></span>, <span class=3D"texhtml=
"><b>v</b><sub>2</sub></span>, ..., <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>v</b><sub><i=
>n</i></sub></span> with associated eigenvalues <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=
=CE=BB</i><sub>1</sub></span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BB</i><sub>2<=
/sub></span>, ..., <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BB</i><sub><i>n</i></sub>=
</span>. The eigenvalues need not be distinct. Define a <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_matrix" title=3D"Square matrix">square matrix<=
/a> <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">Q</span> whos=
e columns are the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"=
>n</span> linearly independent eigenvectors of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar"=
 style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span>,
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle Q=3D{\begin{bmatrix}\mathbf {v} _{1}&amp;\mathbf {v} _{2}&amp;\=
cdots &amp;\mathbf {v} _{n}\end{bmatrix}}.}">
