<p>Matrices with entries only along the main diagonal are called <i><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagonal_matrices" class=3D"mw-redirect" =
title=3D"Diagonal matrices">diagonal matrices</a></i>.  The eigenvalues of =
a diagonal matrix are the diagonal elements themselves. Consider the matrix
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle A=3D{\begin{bmatrix}1&amp;0&amp;0\\0&amp;2&amp;0\\0&amp;0&amp;3=
\end{bmatrix}}.}">
