</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BB</i><sub>2</sub> =3D 2</span>, an=
d <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>=CE=BB</i><sub>3</sub> =3D 3</span>. These roo=
ts are the diagonal elements as well as the eigenvalues of&nbsp;<span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span>.
</p><p>Each diagonal element corresponds to an eigenvector whose only nonze=
ro component is in the same row as that diagonal element. In the example, t=
he eigenvalues correspond to the eigenvectors,
