<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Triangular_matrix_example">=
Triangular matrix example</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DEigenvalues_and_eigenvectors&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D=
18" title=3D"Edit section: Triangular matrix example"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>A matrix whose elements above the main diagonal are all zero is called a=
 <i>lower <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triangular_matrix" title=
=3D"Triangular matrix">triangular matrix</a></i>, while a matrix whose elem=
ents below the main diagonal are all zero is called an <i>upper triangular =
matrix</i>.  As with diagonal matrices, the eigenvalues of triangular matri=
ces are the elements of the main diagonal.
</p><p>Consider the lower triangular matrix,
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle A=3D{\begin{bmatrix}1&amp;0&amp;0\\1&amp;2&amp;0\\2&amp;3&amp;3=
\end{bmatrix}}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow>
            <mo>[</mo>
            <mtable rowspacing=3D"4pt" columnspacing=3D"1em">
              <mtr>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>0</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>0</mn>
                </mtd>
              </mtr>
              <mtr>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>0</mn>
                </mtd>
              </mtr>
              <mtr>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>2</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mtd>
                <mtd>
                  <mn>3</mn>
                </mtd>
              </mtr>
            </mtable>
            <mo>]</mo>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A=3D{\begin{b=
matrix}1&amp;0&amp;0\\1&amp;2&amp;0\\2&amp;3&amp;3\end{bmatrix}}.}</annotat=
ion>
