ub><i>A</i></sub> =3D</span> <span class=3D"texhtml">4 =3D <i>n</i></span>,=
 the order of the characteristic polynomial and the dimension of <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span>.
</p><p>On the other hand, the <i><dfn>geometric multiplicity</dfn></i> of t=
he eigenvalue 2 is only 1, because its eigenspace is spanned by just one ve=
ctor <span class=3D"texhtml">[0 1 =E2=88=921 1]<sup>T</sup></span> and is t=
herefore 1-dimensional. Similarly, the geometric multiplicity of the eigenv=
