>Hilbert</a> or <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banach_space" titl=
e=3D"Banach space">Banach space</a>. A widely used class of linear transfor=
mations acting on infinite-dimensional spaces are the <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_operator" title=3D"Differential operator">=
differential operators</a> on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Func=
tion_space" title=3D"Function space">function spaces</a>. Let <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">D</span> be a linear differe=
ntial operator on the space <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elemen=
t-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
ext=3D"{\displaystyle C^{\infty }(\mathbb {R} )}">
