        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mover>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mo>=C2=A8<!-- =C2=A8 --></mo>
            </mover>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>k</mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m{\ddot {x}}=
=3D-kx}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/93228b5a83409e6b2ed3800bfa207d9d7c61d63f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.505ex; width:10.818ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle m=
{\ddot {x}}=3D-kx}"></span>
</p><p>That is, acceleration is proportional to position (i.e., we expect <=
span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> to be sin=
usoidal in time).
</p><p>In <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span=
> dimensions, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</=
span> becomes a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_matrix" title=
=3D"Mass matrix">mass matrix</a> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">k</span> a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sti=
ffness_matrix" title=3D"Stiffness matrix">stiffness matrix</a>. Admissible =
solutions are then a linear combination of solutions to the <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Generalized_eigenvalue_problem" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Generalized eigenvalue problem">generalized eigenvalue proble=
m</a>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle kx=3D\omega ^{2}mx}">
